            <h3>Privacy Policy ("Policy")</h3>
            <br>
            <span id="section0">
              This Policy sets out the manner in which LAD GLOBAL collects, uses, manages and protects personal data (as defined below) in compliance with the provisions of the Personal Data Protection Act 2012 and General Data Protection Regulation 2018.<br><br>
              This policy applies to all individuals (as defined below) who provide LAD GLOBAL with personal data or whose personal data is otherwise collected, used and/or disclosed by LAD GLOBAL in connection with and/or for the purpose of its operations.<br><br>
              This policy supplements but does not supersede or replace any previous consent which an individual may have provided to LAD GLOBAL, nor does it affects any rights that LAD GLOBAL may have at law in connection with the collection, use and/or disclosure of any individual's personal data. Subject to that, LAD GLOBAL will not collect any personal data from an individual unless the individual has voluntarily chosen to provide.<br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL may from time to time update this policy to ensure it is consistent with its future developments or business purposes or to accommodate future changes to applicable legal or regulatory requirements. All updates to this policy will be published at www.ladglobal.com and appropriate notifications of any material revisions will be issued to the relevant persons. Subject to an individual's rights at law, the prevailing terms of the policy from time to time shall apply. By continuing their relationship with LAD GLOBAL after any amendments have been introduced and published, individuals shall be deemed to have accepted the policy as amended.<br><br>
              For the avoidance of doubt, this policy forms part of the terms and conditions, if any, governing an individual's specific relationship with LAD GLOBAL ("Terms and Conditions") and should be read in conjunction with such terms and conditions. In the event of any conflict or inconsistency between the provisions of this policy and terms and conditions, the provisions of the terms and conditions shall prevail to the fullest extent permissible by law.<br><br>
              <b><u>Definitions</u></b><br><br>
              <b>“Data Protection Officer”</b> means the person designated to be responsible for ensuring that LAD GLOBAL complies with the PDPA and GDPR;<br><br>
              <b>“DNC Registry”</b> means the Do-Not-Call registry maintained by the Personal Data Protection Commission, pursuant to the PDPA and GDPR;<br><br>
              <b>“Event Participants”</b> means users who participate in or attend events or programmes organised or sponsored by LAD GLOBAL from time to time;<br><br>
              <b>“Individuals”</b> means natural persons, whether living or deceased, and “Individual” means any of them;<br><br>
              <b>"Users”</b> mean the users of LAD GLOBAL from time to time;<br><br>
              <b>“PDPA”</b> means the Personal Data Protection Act 2012;<br><br>
              <b>“GDPR”</b> means the General Data Protection Regulation 2018;<br><br>
              <b>“Personal Data”</b> means data that is capable of identifying a natural person, whether on its own or in conjunction with other data that is accessible to LAD GLOBAL;<br><br>
              <b>“Personnel”</b> shall include any person engaged under a contract of service or contract for service with LAD GLOBAL, management personnel, permanent or temporary employees, as well as trainees, interns and volunteers engaged by LAD GLOBAL from time to time; and<br><br>
              <b>“Potential Personnel”</b> shall include any Individual who has submitted an application to be engaged by LAD GLOBAL as employees.<br><br>
            </span> 
            <span id="section1">
              <b><u>Personal Data Collected by LAD GLOBAL</u></b><br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL will only collect, use or disclose personal data about an individual which it reasonably considers necessary for the relevant purposes underlying such collection, use or disclosure. Depending on the specific nature of an individual's interaction with LAD GLOBAL, personal data which LAD GLOBAL collects, uses or discloses concerning an individual may variously include the following:<br>
              <ul class="unordereddisc">
                <li>Individual's name, gender and contact particulars, including telephone number(s), residential/mailing address(es) and email address;</li>
                <li>Individual's identification documents (such as, NRIC or passport numbers), and applicable visa or permits (such as employment pass, work permit, permanent residency status);</li>
                <li>Individual’s employment history and academic qualifications;</li>
                <li>Individual's CPF, credit card or bank account;</li>
                <li>Name and contact particulars of the individual's next-of-kin;</li>
                <li>Individual's personal preferences or other special requests or special conditions applicable to the individual;</li>
                <li>Individual's hobbies or special interest areas;</li>
                <li>Individual's network usage data and other information gathered automatically by our computer systems, including the individual's computer IP address, links visited and other activities conducted online or using our computer systems;</li>
                <li>Photographs and video or CCTV recordings of the individual; and</li>
                <li>Other information which the individual may provide to LAD GLOBAL, from time to time, in the course of such individual's interaction with LAD GLOBAL.</li>
              </ul>
              <br>
            </span>
            <span id="section2">
              <b><u>How LAD GLOBAL collects Personal Data</u></b><br><br>
              Generally, LAD GLOBAL may collect Personal Data about an Individual in one or more of the following ways:<br><br>
              <ul class="unordereddisc">
                <li>Application or registration forms submitted by the Individual;</li>
                <li>Correspondence, emails or electronic messages submitted by the Individual to LAD GLOBAL or otherwise posted on LAD GLOBAL’s website(s) and social media account (s);</li>
                <li>Individual’s verbal communications with LAD GLOBAL Personnel;</li>
                <li>Surveys conducted with and/or feedback received from an Individual;</li>
                <li>Individual’s access to and/or use or navigation of LAD GLOBAL’s website(s) and its computer network and the use of cookies;</li>
                <li>Recordings of the Individual when attending at LAD GLOBAL’s premises or at any events or programmes organised by LAD GLOBAL;</li>
                <li>Through third party business partners or associates of LAD GLOBAL; and</li>
                <li>Individuals’ submission of his/her Personal Data to LAD GLOBAL for any other reason related to LAD GLOBAL’s ordinary course of operations.</li>
              </ul>
              <br>
            </span>
            <span id="section3">
              <b><u>Purposes for which LAD GLOBAL may collect, use and/or disclose Personal Data</u></b><br><br>
              Generally, LAD GLOBAL may collect, use and/or disclose Personal Data about an Individual for one or more of the following purposes:<br><br>
              <u>Individuals and Users</u>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>Administering and managing Users relationships with LAD GLOBAL, including the provision of services to Users;</li>
                <li>providing Individuals, and Users with information about services, facilities and/or other benefits being offered or made available by LAD GLOBAL to Public and Users;</li>
                <li>providing Individuals and Users with information about third party and/or external vendor/supplier promotions, deals and/or other services being offered or made available to Users, through partnerships, associations and/or other collaborations involving such third parties or external vendors/suppliers and LAD GLOBAL;</li>
                <li>Organising and/or facilitating events or programmes involving Individuals and Users /or verifying the eligibility of such Individuals and Users to participate in such events or programmes;</li>
                <li>Producing reports, conduct market research and data analysis;</li>
                <li>Tailoring activities or services available to match Users preferences; and</li>
                <li>Transmitting Personal Data to third parties engaged by or working in collaboration with LAD GLOBAL to facilitate any of the above-mentioned purposes.</li>
              </ol>
              <u>Personnel</u><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>Administering and managing Personnel relationships with LAD GLOBAL, including the provision of services to Personnel;</li>
                <li>Evaluating the performance of Personnel;</li>
                <li>Undertaking staff training and quality assurance activities;</li>
                <li>Providing Personnel with services, facilities and/or other benefits being offered or made available by LAD GLOBAL to such Personnel as well as information about such services, facilities and benefits; and</li>
                <li>Transmitting Personal Data to third parties engaged by or working in collaboration with LAD GLOBAL to facilitate any of the above-mentioned purposes.</li>
              </ol>
              <u>Potential Personnel</u><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>Administering and managing LAD GLOBAL’s relationship with Potential Personnel; and</li>
                <li>Evaluating the suitability and eligibility of Potential Personnel to be engaged by LAD GLOBAL;</li>
              </ol>
              <u>Event Participants</u><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>Administering and managing the event participant’s relationship with LAD GLOBAL;</li>
                <li>Verifying the identity and eligibility of event participants;</li>
                <li>Promotional and publicity purposes, including recording videos or taking photographs of participants at events; and</li>
                <li>Transmitting Personal Data to third parties engaged by or working in collaboration with LAD GLOBAL to facilitate any of the above-mentioned purposes.</li>
              </ol>
              <u>Visitors and users of LAD GLOBAL’s facilities</u><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>Recording and verifying the identity of visitors to LAD GLOBAL’s premises and users of LAD GLOBAL’s facilities; and </li>
                <li>Monitoring the activities of visitors to LAD GLOBAL’s premises and users of LAD GLOBAL’s facilities.</li>
              </ol>
              <u>General business purposes</u><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>Managing the administrative and business operations of LAD GLOBAL;  </li>
                <li>Facilitating the completion of transactions with Individuals;</li>
                <li>Responding to complaints, queries and/or requests;</li>
                <li>Conducting market research for statistical profiling and other purposes in order to improve LAD GLOBAL’s services; </li>
                <li>Safety and security purposes;</li>
                <li>Preventing, detecting or investigating any actual or crime, fraud, misconduct, unlawful action, breach or dispute;</li>
                <li>Record-keeping purposes; </li>
                <li>Accounting or auditing purposes;</li>
                <li>Legal purposes (including but not limited to obtaining legal advice and dispute resolution); and</li>
                <li>Complying with laws, regulations, codes or guidelines binding on LAD GLOBAL, including disclosures to regulatory authorities or other public bodies; and</li>
                <li>Transmitting Personal Data to third parties engaged by or working in collaboration with LAD GLOBAL to facilitate any of the above-mentioned purposes.</li>
              </ol>
              <u>Purposes reasonably related to any of the above purposes</u><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>For any purposes reasonably related and/or ancillary to any of the abovementioned purposes.</li>
              </ol>
              <u>Purposes for which specific consent was obtained</u><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>For any other purposes for which the Individual’s consent was specifically given or obtained.</li>
              </ol>
              <br/>
            </span>
            <span id="section12">
              <b><u>Provision of Data Breach Notifications</u></b><br><br>
              Data Protection Officer will notify the stakeholders affected by the data breach within 72 hours of learning of the breach and will provide specific details of the breach such as the nature of it and the approximate number of data subjects affected.<br><br>
            </span>
            <span id="section4">
              <b><u>Consent</u></b><br><br>
              Unless otherwise authorised under the PDPA, GDPR or any other applicable law, LAD GLOBAL will not collect, use or disclose an Individual’s Personal Data without his/her consent.<br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL will take reasonable steps to highlight the purposes relevant to an Individual, by appropriate means, at the point or time of collection of the Personal Data from such Individual, including:<br><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>Via express provisions in contracts, application forms and/or registration forms to be signed with or submitted to LAD GLOBAL;</li>
                <li>Via notifications on LAD GLOBAL’s websites; and</li>
                <li>Through the course of verbal communications.</li>
              </ol><br>
              Where feasible, LAD GLOBAL will inform the Individual of purposes that are intrinsic to the relationship between LAD GLOBAL or to the provision of services to such Individual, as well as purposes that are optional.<br><br>
              In so far as any purpose(s) are intrinsic to the relationship or provision of services, LAD GLOBAL reserves the right to decline to engage in the relevant relationship or to provide the relevant services to the Individual if he or she does not consent to LAD GLOBAL’s collection, use or disclosure of his/her Personal Data for such purpose.<br><br>
              Individuals who:<br><br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>Voluntarily provide their Personal Data to LAD GLOBAL for the specified purposes;</li>
                <li>Use or access LAD GLOBAL’s website(s) or computer network;</li>
                <li>Enter LAD GLOBAL’s premises or using any of the facilities thereon; and/or</li>
                <li>Attend or participate in events or programmes organised by LAD GLOBAL.</li>
              </ol><br>
              Will be deemed to agree and consent to LAD GLOBAL collecting, using and/or disclosing their Personal Data in the manner and for the purposes set forth in this Privacy Policy.<br><br>
              An Individual who provides LAD GLOBAL with Personal Data relating to a third party (e.g. information of his/her spouse or children) for any particular purpose, represents to LAD GLOBAL that he/she has obtained the consent of the relevant third party to LAD GLOBAL collecting, using or disclosing such Personal Data for the relevant purpose.<br><br>
              In so far as LAD GLOBAL collects Personal Data of an Individual from any third party(ies), LAD GLOBAL will take reasonable steps to inform the relevant third party(ies) of LAD GLOBAL’s purposes for collecting the Personal Data and to verify that consent from the Individual has been obtained by the relevant third party(ies) to such disclosure for the intended purpose.<br><br>
            </span>
            <span id="section5">
              <b><u>Withdrawal of Consent</u></b><br><br>
              Any Individual who wishes to withdraw his/her consent to any use or disclosure of his/her Personal Data by LAD GLOBAL as set out in this Policy may do so by notifying LAD GLOBAL’s Data Protection Officer at info@ladglobal.com. LAD GLOBAL may require up to 3 weeks from the date of the Individual’s notification to respond and effect any change.<br><br>
              Depending on the extent to which an Individual withdraws consent to any or all use or disclosure of his or her Personal Data by LAD GLOBAL, such withdrawal of consent may result in LAD GLOBAL’s inability to provide services to the Individual and may be considered as a termination by the Individual of any agreement between LAD GLOBAL and the Individual. LAD GLOBAL’s legal rights and remedies are expressly reserved in such event.<br><br>
            </span>
            <span id="section6">
              <b><u>Verification of Personal Data & Notification of Changes</u></b><br><br>
              Where feasible, LAD GLOBAL will take reasonable steps to verify the accuracy of Personal Data received at the point of collection but Individuals remain primarily responsible and liable to ensure that all Personal Data submitted by them to LAD GLOBAL is complete and accurate. Information voluntarily submitted by an Individual to LAD GLOBAL shall prima facie be deemed complete and accurate.<br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL will also take reasonable steps to periodically verify Personal Data in its possession, taking into account the exigencies of its operations, but Individuals are nonetheless required to notify LAD GLOBAL, from time to time, of any applicable changes to such Personal Data.<br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL shall not be held liable for any inability on its part to provide services to an Individual who fails to ensure that his/her Personal Data submitted to LAD GLOBAL is complete and accurate or who fails to notify LAD GLOBAL of any relevant changes to such Personal Data.<br><br>
            </span>
            <span id="section7">
              <b><u>Policy on telephone numbers registered with the DNC Registry</u></b><br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL is prohibited from sending unsolicited telemarketing messages (“specified messages”) to Singapore telephone numbers through voice calls, text or fax messages registered on the DNC Registers unless LAD GLOBAL has obtained the relevant Individual’s clear and unambiguous consent in written or other accessible forms.<br><br>
              In compliance with the PDPA, LAD GLOBAL will not send specified messages to telephone numbers that appear on the DNC Registry unless the relevant Individual has given LAD GLOBAL clear and unambiguous consent to do so.<br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL will continue to contact Individuals at the telephone numbers provided to LAD GLOBAL in the limited circumstances allowed under the DNC Registry even if these telephone number are registered with the DNC Registry. Individuals who do not wish to receive such messages may notify LAD GLOBAL’s Data Protection Officer at [info@ladglobal.com].<br><br>
            </span>
            <span id="section8">
              <b><u>Activities undertaken prior to 4 May 2017</u></b><br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL may use Personal Data of an Individual that was collected before 4 May 2017 for purposes for which the Personal Data was collected unless consent is withdrawn by that Individual.<br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL will continue to use Personal Data of Users, which had been collected before 4 May 2017, for its general business purposes and purposes relating to Users. Users who wish to withdraw their consent to LAD GLOBAL’s use of their Personal Data may contact LAD GLOBAL’s Data Protection Officer at [info@ladglobal.com].<br><br>
            </span>
            <span id="section9">
              <b><u>Protection of Personal Data</u></b><br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL shall make reasonable security arrangements to prevent unauthorised access, collection, use, disclosure, copying, modification, disposal or similar risks to Personal Data in its possession.<br><br>
              If LAD GLOBAL transfers Personal Data outside Singapore, European Union (EU) and European Economic Area (EEA), LAD GLOBAL will take reasonable steps to ensure that such Personal Data transferred receives a standard of protection comparable to the protection received under the PDPA & GDPR.<br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL will ensure that third parties who receive Personal Data from LAD GLOBAL protect such Personal Data in a manner consistent with this Policy and not use such Personal Data for any purposes other than those specified by LAD GLOBAL, by incorporating appropriate contractual terms in its written agreements with these third parties.  <br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL is not responsible in any way for the security and/or management of Personal Data shared by Individuals with third party websites accessible via links on LAD GLOBAL’s website.<br><br>
            </span>
            <span id="section10">
              <b><u>Contacting LAD GLOBAL—Access and Correction of Personal Data</u></b><br><br>
              Any Individual who:<br>
              <ol class="orderedbrackets">
                <li>has questions or feedback relating to this Policy;</li>
                <li>would like to obtain access to his/her Personal Data held by LAD GLOBAL;</li>
                <li>would like to obtain information about the ways in which his/her Personal Data held by LAD GLOBAL has been or may have been used or disclosed by LAD GLOBAL in the year preceding the request; and/or</li>
                <li>would like to update or make corrections to his/her Personal Data held by LAD GLOBAL, should contact LAD GLOBAL’s Data Protection Officer at info@ladglobal.com.</li>
              </ol><br>
              Individuals should note that LAD GLOBAL is not required, under the PDPA, to provide access and correction to Personal Data in certain situations.<br><br>
              The PDPA allows and LAD GLOBAL reserves the right to charge a reasonable fee for the handling and/or processing of access requests by an Individual pursuant to paragraphs (b) or (c) above.<br><br>
              LAD GLOBAL may require up to 3 weeks from the date of the Individual’s request to respond and effect any change.<br><br>   
            </span>
            <span id="section11">
              <b><u>Governing Law </u></b><br><br>
              This Policy shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of Singapore. Any dispute arising out of or in connection with this Policy including any question regarding its existence, validity or termination, shall be referred to and finally resolved by the Courts of Singapore.<br><br>   
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
